{
  "texts": [
    "Overall academic outcomes may consider additional aspects of academic success, such as behavior, attendance, and social-emotional development.",
    "On the other hand, \"predicting students who can be at risk of failure\" is defined as the one who is in danger of not passing a course or grade level because they do not meet academic requirements.",
    "Administrators and instructors can identify these students through attendance records, behavioral data, or assessment data.",
    "In addition, students who are at risk of failure have incomplete assignments, lower test grades, or a history of academic difficulties.",
    "This may be due to either a lack of interest or engagement or motivation, poor attendance, inadequate support, or learning difficulties Brdesee et al (2022); Huang et al (2022); Liu et al (2022c); Waheed et al (2022)."
  ]
}